==Strengths and weaknesses==
'''Equipping a [[nose peg]] or [[slayer helmet]] is required when fighting aberrant spectres; if you do not, they will use a special attack which will always hit, even through [[Protection Prayers]], and drain your combat stats extremely quickly. Boosts cannot be used to equip a nose peg so level 60 Slayer or a slayer helmet is required.'''

They attack using [[Magic]], so the [[Protect from Magic]] prayer can be helpful, or magic resistant armour such as [[dragonhide armour|dragonhide]]. As an [[undead]] monster the [[Salve amulet]] or [[Salve amulet (e)]] can be worn for a damage and accuracy bonus when fighting them. The bonus from the salve amulet does not stack with a [[slayer helmet]]/[[black mask]] and when both are worn, in which case only the salve amulet effect will apply.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1242015573325877248|date=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/vVKUG|archivedate=23 March 2020|quote=Salve effects override the Slayer helm / black mask effects (because they're either identical or bigger). So you'll get bonuses for Void, then multiplied up by the Salve effect, then multiplied up again for the dragonbane bonus.}}

'''Note:''' It is possible to use a [[dwarf multicannon]] inside the [[Stronghold Slayer Cave]]. This is recommended for fastest slayer experience.

It is possible to safespot in the [[Slayer Tower]] by standing on the brick pile just west of the [[Agility]] chain shortcut and pulling spectres just in front of the suit of armour from the room south of the shortcut. A [[crossbow (weapon)|crossbow]]'s [[rapid]] attack style will be able to target aberrant spectres from this distance, making it a very useful spot. It is also possible to wait out the 10 minute hostility period with minimal risk by hiding beside the table in the north-west corner. You may be attacked occasionally, but it won't be often. This works well in connection with the safespotting /trapping process.

It is also possible to [[safespot]] one of the aberrant spectres by using the south-eastern corner of the wall of the staircase-room.

In the Stronghold Slayer Cave, they can be safespotted around a section of the cave wall in the middle of the eastern part of the dungeon.

[[File:Aberrant spectre safespot.png|alt=Safespot in Stronghold Slayer Cave.|thumb|295x300px|Safespot in the Stronghold Slayer Cave.]]

All safespots only work with [[Ranged]] or [[Magic]], since there must be at least six spaces between the player and the aberrant spectre to avoid their attack range. [[Halberd]]s or thrown weapons such as [[throwing knives]] and [[throwing axe]]s do not have a long enough attack range to safespot. In addition, these safespots are only usable when the spectres are non-aggressive, since nearby spectres will attack the player and prevent them from killing the trapped spectre.

